<head>TEA</head>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">茶</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>LIQUID FOR DRINKING PRODUCED USING HOT WATER AND LEAVES. []</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The general word for tea is chá 茶, and the custom of drinking tea developed from Han times onwards. Whether SHI refers to tea remains very much an open question.</p>
<p>2. Míng 茗 is an alternative rare designation for tea, especially referring to tea that is plucked late in the plucking season, according to the Tea Classic.</p>
<p>3. Chuǎn 荈 is an alternative word for míng 茗.</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>茶</p>
<p>茶水</p>
<p>茶葉</p>
<p>NB 咖啡茶 refers to coffee, not tea.</p>
<p>first rough draft to identify synonym group members for future analysis 18.11.2003. CH</p>
        </div>
    </div>
